## Welcome, Captain — Fresh Principal Bootstrap

You are the captain instance for principal **{{PRINCIPAL_DISPLAY_NAME}}** in repo **{{REPO_NAME}}**. This is your first session. There is no prior history to inherit — you're starting from a clean slate.

### What this handoff is

This file was scaffolded by `/principal-create` so that your first `/session-resume` has context to read instead of an empty file. Once you finish your first real session, the normal handoff tool (`./agency/tools/handoff write`) will replace this bootstrap with real session state.

### Your sandbox

- **Principal root:** `usr/{{PRINCIPAL_NAME}}/`
- **Captain dir:** `usr/{{PRINCIPAL_NAME}}/captain/`
- **Principal CLAUDE.md:** `usr/{{PRINCIPAL_NAME}}/CLAUDE-PRINCIPAL.md` — read this first, it defines who {{PRINCIPAL_DISPLAY_NAME}} is and what they care about
- **Handoff file:** `usr/{{PRINCIPAL_NAME}}/captain/captain-handoff.md` (this file)

### ISCP state

Your ISCP DB is empty for this principal — **no inherited dispatches, no flags, no pending work**. The first dispatches and flags you create or receive will populate it. Don't be alarmed when `/dispatch list` and `/flag list` return nothing.

### First actions — do these in order

1. **Read your principal definition** — `usr/{{PRINCIPAL_NAME}}/CLAUDE-PRINCIPAL.md`. This is your source of truth for what {{PRINCIPAL_DISPLAY_NAME}} wants, their voice, their priorities.
2. **Baseline the repo** — run `./agency/tools/agency-health` to see fleet state: workstreams, agents, worktrees, severity. Record anything red or yellow.
3. **Read the bootloader** — `agency/CLAUDE-THEAGENCY.md` if you haven't already. It's your operating manual.
4. **Pick a first workstream** — either:
   - Adopt an existing workstream under `agency/workstreams/` that aligns with {{PRINCIPAL_DISPLAY_NAME}}'s goals, or
   - Use `/workstream-create` to scaffold a new one.
5. **Start the dispatch monitor** — run `/monitor-dispatches` so you get real-time notification of incoming ISCP traffic. **Do not skip this.** It is the #1 thing new captains miss.
6. **Write your first real handoff** — at session end, run `/session-end` (or `./claude/tools/handoff write`). That archives this bootstrap to `history/` and replaces it with real session state.

### Cross-repo collaboration

If {{PRINCIPAL_DISPLAY_NAME}} participates in cross-repo dispatches with other agencies (monofolk, etc.), the `/collaborate` skill is your interface. Check `agency/REFERENCE-ISCP-PROTOCOL.md` for the 4-segment addressing model (`org/repo/principal/agent`). No inbound cross-repo traffic yet — you'll wire that up when there's something to coordinate.

### Key skills to remember

| Skill | When |
|-------|------|
| `/session-resume` | Every session start |
| `/session-end` | Every session end |
| `/monitor-dispatches` | Start of every session (persistent) |
| `/agency-health` | Baseline + before releases |
| `/git-safe-commit` | Every commit (never raw `git commit`) |
| `/dispatch` | Outgoing work to agents / other principals |
| `/flag` | Quick-capture observations for later 1B1 |
| `/handoff` | Never write handoff files by hand |

### What NOT to do on day one

- Don't push to origin until you've talked to {{PRINCIPAL_DISPLAY_NAME}} about what's ready
- Don't claim work is "complete" for anything uncommitted
- Don't skip the handoff tool — hookify will block raw `git commit` and manual handoff edits
- Don't rebase — merge, never rebase

